.SH NAME
Window.gamepadconnected_event \- Window: gamepadconnected event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]gamepadconnected\f[R] event is fired when the browser detects
that a gamepad has been connected or the first time a button/axis of the
gamepad is used.
.PP
The event will not fire if disallowed by the document\(cqs
\f[CR]gamepad\f[R] Permissions Policy.
.PP
This event is not cancelable and does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqgamepadconnected\(dq, (event) => { })

ongamepadconnected = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EXAMPLES
To be informed when a gamepad is connected, you can add a handler to the
window using \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], like this:
.IP
.EX
window.addEventListener(\(dqgamepadconnected\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// All buttons and axes values can be accessed through\f[R]
  \f[B]const\f[R] gamepad = event.gamepad;
});
.EE
.PP
Alternatively, you can use the \f[CR]window.ongamepadconnected\f[R]
event handler property to establish a handler for the
\f[CR]gamepadconnected\f[R] event:
.IP
.EX
